==English==
===Etymology===
From the Spanish [[juzgado]] (pronounced 'χusgáðo' in careful speech, but 'χusgáo' in relaxed or rapid speech), meaning[[court]], [[courthouse]].

===Noun===
'''hoosegow''' (uncountable)
#{{slang}} [[jail]]
#:''He was so drunk they took him to the '''hoosegow''' to dry out.

